The Lagos state government on Friday announced the discharge of four coronavirus patients after making full recovery from the novel virus. “More great news from our Infectious Disease Hospital as 4 patients; 3 females and 1 male have recovered fully, tested negative twice and have been discharged,” Lagos State governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu tweeted. This comes hours after 11 patients were also discharged. So far the state has discharged 23 of its 98 confirmed cases. Nigeria have recorded 190 cases the dreaded virus and 24 have been discharged nationwide. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .